ices.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">Transparency of and rep</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold">orting by commissioners to date</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">8.1</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">I inherited only half a team, mainly ex Police Authority staff, who did not appreciate how to be transparent in the way that elected officials should be. </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">  </span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">8.2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">In addition, </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">the electronic processes were</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">n</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">o</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">t there either</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> but this is now addressed</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">8.3</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">But we have got there, and I am confident that </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">I </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">and the Force are now as transparent a</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s we could be.  Indeed it was re</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">assuring that Bernard Rix (COPACC) stated that my office is one of the best at being transparent nationally. </span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt; font-weight:bold; text-decoration:underline">Conclusion</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">9.1</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">I feel I have highlighted many positives in this submission, and I have highlighted blockages too.</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> I am surprised that your questioning has not focussed at all on public engagement, arguably the biggest part of a PCC</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">s role.  For democracy to be effective, it has to be visibly effective.  I attend a public forum every two weeks, hold PCC surgeries and I have recruited </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">six voluntary advocates, who are my “eyes and ears” in various communities, including the older community and the Polish</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt"> communities</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">9.2</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">There is so much more that the role of the PCC can achieve, given the time, the right resources and the opportunity.  I believe I make a difference and I will continue to work hard to keep the people of Dorset safe.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt; text-align:justify"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">9.3</span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">              </span><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">To detail all of the work undertaken in the year is difficult within 3000 words and I am happy to expand on the areas above and other areas I am influencing by appearing before your Committee.</span></p><p style="margin:0pt 0pt 0pt 35.45pt; text-align:justify; text-indent:-35.45pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">&#xa0;</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Martyn Underhill</span></p><p style="margin:0pt"><span style="font-family:Arial; font-size:11pt">Police and Crim